

    ●Both of them must be
    the first statement
    in the constructor.
    We need to pick one
    or the other.
     Useage:

    ● super() will call
    the super/parent class’
    constructor..

    ● super. will let us
    access the parent/super class’
    variables, members, methods, etc.

    ● this() will call a
    constructor from another
    constructor within
    the same class.

    ● this. will access
    instance variables
    and methods.
